excerpt: Traditional Zen Buddhist temple located on a hill & featuring picturesque gardens & mountain views.
detail_description: Nestled on a hill with stunning mountain views, Truc Lam Buddhist Monastery in Dalat offers a serene escape for those seeking tranquility and spiritual enlightenment. Surrounded by picturesque gardens and located near Tuyen Lam Lake, the monastery provides a peaceful setting for meditation and self-reflection. Visitors can also take a scenic cable car ride from Robin Hill to the monastery, enjoying panoramic views of lush valleys and pine-covered hills along the way.
name: Truc Lam Buddhist Monastery
address: WC3M+7MG, Trúc Lâm Yên Tử, Phường 3, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

detail_description: Xuan Huong Lake, located in the heart of Dalat, is a popular spot for both locals and tourists. Visitors can enjoy leisurely walks around the lake, relax on benches or grassy areas, rent boats, or take a horse-drawn carriage ride. The picturesque surroundings include pine forests and flower gardens. However, issues such as garbage collection and illegal fishing have been noted.
name: Xuan Huong Lake
address: Dalat, Lam Dong, Vietnam

excerpt: Large, striking pagoda known for its intricate mosaics made from broken glass & pottery shards.
detail_description: Chùa Linh Phước is a renowned pagoda in Dalat, Vietnam, known for its stunning mosaic art created from shattered glass and pottery. It is a popular attraction along with the Truc Lam Zen Monastery, offering visitors an opportunity to immerse themselves in the tranquility and wisdom of Buddhism. The pagoda's intricate mosaic artwork captivates every visitor, while the monastery provides a serene environment for meditation and self-reflection.
name: Linh Phước Temple
address: WFR5+57X, 120 Tự Phước, Phường 11, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng 550000, Vietnam

excerpt: Surrounded by trees, this sizable man-made lake offers scenic views amid a serene environment.
detail_description: Tuyền Lâm Lake, located in the picturesque city of Da Lat, Vietnam, is a serene man-made lake surrounded by lush trees. Visitors can enjoy scenic views and a tranquil atmosphere while exploring the area. Nearby attractions include the historic palaces and summer home of Bao Dai, the last emperor of Vietnam, as well as the Dalat Palace Golf Club for those interested in golfing or simply admiring the beautiful surroundings.
name: Tuyền Lâm Lake
address: Phường 4, Dalat, Lam Dong, Vietnam

detail_description: Nestled in the picturesque city of Dalat, Vietnam, the Dalat Railway Station stands as a testament to the region's French heritage. This historic station, dating back to 1932 and designed by renowned French architects Moncet and Reveron, is not only the oldest Indochinese station but also holds the distinction of being the highest in altitude within Vietnam at 1,500 meters above sea level.
name: Dalat Railway Station
address: Quang Trung, Phường 9, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: Bustling scenic spot with a small series of waterfalls, a roller coaster, cable car & hiking trails.
detail_description: Datanla Waterfall, located in Dalat, Vietnam, is a bustling and popular spot known for its series of small waterfalls and various activities. It offers a range of attractions such as a roller coaster, cable car, hiking trails, abseiling, rafting, and free jumping. The entrance area is touristy and developed with a packed car park, queues at the ticket office, and a busy restaurant. The waterfall has multiple levels with different activities available at each level.
name: Khu du lịch Thác Datanla
address: QL20 Đèo Prenn, Phường 3, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng 66000, Vietnam

excerpt: Sizable palace of the Vietnam's last emperor, completed in 1938, with tours & landscaped gardens.
detail_description: DINH BẢO ĐẠI III, also known as Bao Dai Summer Palace, is a significant historical site in Da Lat, Vietnam. Built in 1938 by a French architect and a Vietnamese architect, the palace showcases European architectural influences. This two-story mansion holds great historical value and is associated with the Nguyen emperor. Surrounded by landscaped gardens, it offers tours for visitors to explore its glorious history and architectural masterpiece.
name: Bao Dai Palace 3
address: 1 Đường Triệu Việt Vương, Phường 4, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: Landmark pink church in a serene setting featuring landscaped gardens & a small shop.
detail_description: Domaine de Marie, also known as Vinh Son Church or Mai Anh Church, is a landmark pink church located in a serene setting just 1km southwest of Dalat city center. Established in 1944, this architectural gem combines seventeenth-century European design with Vietnamese folk architecture. The church sits atop a hill and is surrounded by beautifully landscaped gardens, making it a unique and picturesque attraction in Dalat.
name: Domaine de Marie
address: 1 Ngô Quyền, Phường 6, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: Romantic park with whimsical art, ornate gardens & a lake with swan-shaped boats.
detail_description: Valley of Love in Dalat is a unique and popular tourist attraction, offering a massive park for visitors to explore. It's an ideal spot for a leisurely excursion, perfect for stretching your legs on a sunny morning in Dalat.
name: Valley Of Love
address: 3-5-7 Đường Mai Anh Đào, Phường 8, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

detail_description: Nestled about 20 kilometers from the heart of Dalat, Cau Dat Tea Village sprawls across a vast 230-hectare area at an elevation of 1650 meters above sea level. This picturesque destination is renowned for its stunning green tea gardens that create a mesmerizing backdrop under the radiant sun. Visitors can also enjoy breathtaking panoramic views of the expansive tea hills while savoring a cup of coffee at the unique Dalat Cau Dat Farm cafe.
name: Cau Dat Tea Village
address: Đất, Thôn, Cầu, Xuân Trường, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: Busy collection of vendors selling household items, dry goods & prepared regional dishes.
detail_description: Da Lat Night Market is a lively collection of vendors offering household items, dry goods, and regional dishes. It's a perfect spot to sample local street food and soak in the vibrant nightlife. Nearby attractions like Lam Vien Square, Da Lat Train Station, and French Quarter showcase French colonial architecture and offer great photo opportunities. For those interested in art sculptures, Clay Tunnel and Crazy House Da Lat are worth a visit.
name: Da Lat Night Market
address: Đường Nguyễn Thị Minh Khai, Phường 1, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: 2 artful, colorful glass structures in a park & garden with a subterranean shopping center.
detail_description: Quảng trường Lâm Viên, situated in the heart of the flower city, is a well-known attraction for both tourists and locals. It boasts stunning views of Xuan Huong Lake and is adorned with two vibrant glass structures set within a park and garden. Below the square lies an underground shopping center. The area surrounding Quảng trường Lâm Viên offers a bustling night market for sampling local street food and experiencing lively nightlife.
name: Quảng trường Lâm Viên
address: Phường 10, Tp. Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

detail_description: Chợ đà lạt, also known as Da Lat Market, is a bustling marketplace located on Nguyen Thi Minh Khai street. The market offers a wide variety of food and drinks on its second floor, which are only available during the day and are reasonably priced. Visitors can easily locate this vibrant market using Google Maps, making it a convenient destination for exploration.
name: Da Lat Market
address: Đường Nguyễn Thị Minh Khai, Phường 1, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng 02633, Vietnam

excerpt: Romantic park with whimsical art, ornate gardens & a lake with swan-shaped boats.
detail_description: Valley of Love, located just 6 km from Dalat city in Vietnam, is a romantic park known for its whimsical art, ornate gardens, and a lake where visitors can ride swan-shaped boats. Surrounded by the charming Da Thien lake and endless pine forests, the valley offers a picturesque and poetic scenery that has made it a popular destination for marriage proposals and honeymoons.
name: Valley Of Love
address: 3-5-7 Đường Mai Anh Đào, Phường 8, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: Buddhist temple in scenic hilltop surrounds with a serene vibe, garden & large statue of Buddha.
detail_description: Linh Sơn Pagoda is a serene Buddhist temple located on a hilltop surrounded by picturesque scenery and pine trees. Unlike the bustling Linh Phuoc Pagoda, this temple offers a tranquil atmosphere, making it perfect for a peaceful stroll through its immaculate gardens. Constructed between 1936 and 1940 with contributions from Buddhists worldwide, the pagoda features typical East Asian architecture and houses a 1250 kg bronze statue of Buddha Shakyamuni.
name: Linh Sơn Pagoda
address: 120 Nguyễn Văn Trỗi, Phường 2, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: Romanesque-style Catholic church dating to 1931 with adjacent gardens & elevated views.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Da Lat, Vietnam, the Da Lat Diocese Cathedral, also known as St. Nicholas Cathedral or the Dalat Chicken Church due to its distinctive chicken-topped bell tower, is a stunning example of Romanesque architecture dating back to 1931. This historic church stands as one of the oldest Catholic structures in Vietnam and serves as the cathedral for the local bishop.
name: St. Nicholas Cathedral of Da Lat
address: 15 Đ. Trần Phú, Phường 3, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng 670000, Vietnam

excerpt: Colorful cablecars with panoramic views of the city & a pine forest, plus access to a monastery.
detail_description: The Da Lat Cable Car Station offers a colorful and panoramic journey over the city, pine forests, mountains, lakes, and farms. It provides access to various tourist attractions such as Truc Lam Pagoda, Tuyen Lake, and Datanla waterfalls. At RoBin Hill, visitors can enjoy stunning views of Da Lat city and the pine forested valley before descending 300 meters on a cable car to visit Tuyen Lam Lake.
name: Dalat Cable Car Tourist Area
address: WCFV+5HC, Đồi Robin, Phường 3, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng 66116, Vietnam

detail_description: Prenn Waterfall, located in the town of Ban Nam, Lam Ha ward, 25km from Dalat city to the southwest, is a beautiful natural attraction. The waterfall is over 30m high and about 15m wide with deep caves behind it. It offers an authentic charm and beauty that attracts tourists who want to explore Da Lat's natural form.
name: Prenn waterfall
address: VFHC+385, Phường 3, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: Scenic crescent-shaped 1919 reservoir, a popular city escape named after an anti-establishment poet.
detail_description: Xuan Huong Lake, a crescent-shaped reservoir built in 1919 and named after an anti-establishment poet, offers a romantic and nostalgic atmosphere surrounded by green pine trees. It is fed by the Cam Ly Stream and provides a peaceful escape in central Vietnam's tourist-centric city. Visitors can enjoy leisurely strolls along the 4.5-mile circumference trail, relax at nearby coffee shops, take pedal boats on the lake, or explore the area on tandem bicycles.
name: Xuan Huong Lake
address: Dalat, Lam Dong, Vietnam

detail_description: Nestled in the French Quarter of the hill town, Da Lat Railway Station is a charming structure with colorful glass windows and three high-pointed roofs. Constructed between 1935 and 1938, it boasts a Japanese steam train that travels along 16 km of cog railway tracks. Visitors can embark on a short 7 km journey to Trai Mat Village, enjoying picturesque countryside views en route.
name: Da Lat Railway Station
address: 7a Nguyễn Trãi, Phường 10, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: Grand European-style residence set among pine forest, formerly home to Vietnam's last emperor.
detail_description: Bao Dai Palace 1, also known as Dinh I, is a grand European-style residence nestled in a pine forest in Dalat. This villa was once the home of Vietnam's last emperor and features traditional Hue court interior design. The palace is part of a trio of villas built by King Bao Dai for both work and leisure. Visitors can explore the lavish residence and working spaces of ancient kings from the Nguyen Dynasty while admiring the French colonial architecture that characterizes Dalat City.
name: Bao Dai Palace 1
address: Palace I, Trần Quang Diệu, Phường 10, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

detail_description: Hoa Son Dien Trang Ecotourism Destination is nestled in a primeval forest enveloped in mist, home to ancient trees, gibbons, monkeys, and rare birds. The meticulously tended flower gardens feature a stunning cherry blossom garden with over 4,000 Japanese trees and a rose garden showcasing unique flowers from across Vietnam. Bungalows are tucked away amidst the jungle while the clear blue waters and small waterfalls create picturesque landscapes for photography.
name: Hoa Son Dien Trang Ecotourism Destination
address: Tiểu khu 159 Phường 5 hướng đi đèo, 159 ĐT725, P. 5, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng 670000, Vietnam

detail_description: Khu Du Lịch Lang Biang, located just a short drive from the city center of Da Lat, offers stunning views of the surrounding agricultural region as it rises 2,167 meters above sea level. Visitors can start their hike at the parking lot or take a shuttle closer to the top. At the summit, you can enjoy panoramic views of Da Lat City and its lush landscapes.
name: Khu Du Lịch Lang Biang
address: 305 Langbiang, Thị trấn Lạc Dương, Lạc Dương, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: Đà Lạt, the capital of Lâm Đồng Province in southern Vietnam’s Central Highlands, is centered around a lake and golf course, and surrounded by hills, pine forests, lakes and waterfalls. Known as the “City of Eternal Spring” for its distinctive temperate climate, Đà Lạt was developed as a resort by the French in the early 1900s, and many reminders of its colonial heritage remain.
detail_description: Dalat, also known as the "City of Eternal Spring," is a charming destination in southern Vietnam's Central Highlands. Developed as a resort by the French in the early 1900s, it boasts a temperate climate and stunning natural landscapes. Families visiting Dalat can enjoy its mild temperatures and explore attractions such as roller coasters in the jungle, cable cars to waterfalls, and the unique Crazy House designed by architect Dr. Dang Viet Nga.
name: Dalat
address: Lam Dong, Vietnam

excerpt: Museum showcasing the region's indigenous ethnic culture through costume, handicrafts & art.
detail_description: Lâm Đồng Museum is a fascinating showcase of the indigenous ethnic culture in the region, featuring traditional costumes, handicrafts, and art. Housed in a renovated mansion, this museum offers a deep dive into Vietnamese history and ancient Khmer civilization through relics and artifacts. The well-organized exhibits cover diverse themes such as the province's nature, Da Lat's past and future, local ethnic cultures, and their contributions to anti-colonial resistance.
name: Lam Dong Museum
address: 4 Đ. Hùng Vương, Phường 10, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: Mellow, expansive city park with a yearly festival & a wide variety of plants & flowers.
detail_description: Flower Park, formerly known as Bich Cau Flower Garden, is a must-see attraction in Dalat. Located at the end of Xuan Huong Lake and close to Cu Hill, this 7000 square meter park offers a wide variety of plants and flowers for visitors to enjoy. Renovated and renamed, it boasts the largest selection of flowers in the city and is particularly popular during the annual Flower Festival.
name: Flower Park
address: WCQP+QC, Phường 1, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

detail_description: Đà Lạt Village, also referred to as Chicken Village due to the prominent chicken statue at its entrance, is a charming destination with a unique identity.
name: ĐÀ LẠT VILLAGE
address: 47 KQH Yersin, Phường 9, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

detail_description: Linh Ẩn Pagoda, also known as Linh An Tu, is a popular destination for travelers, especially those from the West who are drawn to its unique Eastern cultural charm. Situated about 30 km from Dalat, this pagoda is one of the five spiritual Buddhist temples in the area and is renowned for its distinctive architecture. Located near the majestic Elephant Falls, it offers a serene setting nestled amidst vast pine forests.
name: Linh An Pagoda
address: Đường Ba Đình, TT. Nam Ban, Lâm Hà, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: Peaceful lake lined with tree-shaded gardens & known for an 18th-century love story.
detail_description: Than Tho Lake, also known as the Lake of Sighs or Lake of Sorrow, is a serene freshwater lake located in Dalat city. The name "Lake of Sighs" originates from an 18th-century love story and the tranquil surroundings that evoke a sense of melancholy. Surrounded by tree-shaded gardens, this picturesque lake has inspired numerous poems and songs due to its fog-wreathed beauty.
name: Than Tho Lake
address: Phường 12, Dalat, Lam Dong, Vietnam

detail_description: Lumiere Da Lat - Light Garden is a popular attraction in Dalat, offering a unique experience with various light exhibits. Visitors can enjoy the opportunity to take stunning photos in the picturesque setting. The venue provides an array of photo opportunities with different light displays, making it ideal for photography enthusiasts. Additionally, visitors have the option to rent traditional Japanese costumes for memorable photo sessions. While it may get crowded at times, visiting during quieter periods allows for a more enjoyable and relaxed experience.
name: Lumiere Da Lat - Light Garden
address: 222B Đường Mai Anh Đào, Phường 8, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: A trail leads up this pine tree-dotted hill known for sunrise views over the misty valley below.
detail_description: Thien Phuc Duc Hill is a must-visit destination for those exploring the enchanting landscapes of Da Lat. Nestled about 10 kilometers from the city center and adjacent to the LangBiang tourist area, this hill offers breathtaking views, especially at sunrise when the mist blankets the valley below. The expansive space dotted with pine trees makes it an ideal spot for camping, photography, and simply soaking in nature's beauty.
name: Thien Phuc Duc Hill
address: Phường 7, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: Compact, basic waterfall & pond with an admission charge & low-key surroundings.
detail_description: Cam Ly Waterfall, located about 2km west of Da Lat city center, is a serene oasis formed by the convergence of two streams. Despite its modest height of around 10 meters, the waterfall's gentle flow and surrounding natural beauty make it a captivating sight. Throughout the year, visitors can enjoy the bubbling white foam of the flowing water and admire the abundance of beautiful flowers in the area. The panorama view includes not only the waterfall but also a perspective of the surrounding large pine forest.
name: Cam Ly Waterfall
address: WCV9+G3P, 8b Đường Hoàng Văn Thụ, Phường 5, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

name: Villa Hang Nga 2
address: 71 Đường Trạng Trình, Phường 9, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: Offbeat guest house with architecture reminiscent of a tree trunk & city views from the roof.
detail_description: Crazy House, also known as Hang Nga Guesthouse, is a must-see attraction in Da Lat. Designed by Vietnamese architect Dang Viet Nga, this offbeat guest house resembles a surreal fairy tale with its unique architecture reminiscent of a giant tree. The design draws inspiration from nature and has been compared to the styles of Antoni Gaudi and Salvador Dali. Visitors can spend about an hour exploring the complex, admiring the winding bridges and sculpted elements throughout.
name: Crazy House - Hang Nga Villa
address: 03 Đ. Huỳnh Thúc Kháng, Phường 4, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng 66115, Vietnam

excerpt: Hillside garden with a tomato farm, flower fields & strawberry picking, plus dog interactions.
detail_description: Puppy Farm, located west of Dalat in Vietnam, is a renowned destination known for providing a nurturing environment for various dog breeds. Visitors can engage in activities such as interacting, playing, and caring for adorable puppies of different sizes and breeds. The farm serves as an educational center where guests can learn about the unique personalities and specific care requirements of each breed. Additionally, it aims to promote responsible pet ownership within the community.
name: Puppy Farm
address: Cam Ly, Măng Lin, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

detail_description: XQ Historical Village is a vast gallery showcasing Vietnamese paintings, abstract photography, and intricate hand embroidery. Situated near the Valley of Love, visitors can explore the picturesque village for an entry fee and opt for a guided tour at an additional cost. The village features flower gardens, ponds, and artisans adorned in traditional costumes, making it a popular spot for photography enthusiasts. The exquisite silk embroidery on display is described as art elevated to new heights, resembling a captivating art gallery within a serene Zen garden.
name: Xq Historical Village
address: 258 Đường Mai Anh Đào, Phường 8, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

detail_description: Canyoning Dalat Tours offer an exhilarating adventure for young travelers seeking thrills in Vietnam. This activity involves cliff swinging, high diving, waterfall sliding, forest trekking, and stream wading. Participants can expect to form strong bonds with fellow adventurers and create lasting memories. With the assistance of specialized tools and training coaches, climbers can conquer precarious waterfall cliffs and experience a sense of triumph at the top.
name: Canyoning Dalat Tours
address: 6A Đường Trần Khánh Dư, Phường 8, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

detail_description: Dalat University, located in Dalat city, Lam Dong, is a public institution that offers multidisciplinary education. Established in 1957 as a Catholic university, it was later taken over by the state. The campus is set on a picturesque pine hill and boasts stunning Southeast Asian scenery. The university's architecture, designed by French architect Moncet, is recognized as one of the world's unique works by the International Union of Architects.
name: Dalat University
address: 1 Đường Phù Đổng Thiên Vương, Phường 8, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

detail_description: Rừng Thông Mơ Farm & Bistro offers a sophisticated fusion dining experience, blending Asian and European flavors in a unique way. The kitchen skillfully combines ingredients to create delicious and high-quality dishes that cannot be found elsewhere. This secluded hideaway in the woods provides an escape from the typical tourist spots in Dalat, with its organic construction and serene atmosphere. Guests can enjoy their meals indoors or outdoors, with the option to explore the nearby organic farm.
name: Rừng Thông Mơ Farm & Bistro
address: Đ. Hoa Hồng, Phường 4, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

detail_description: Fresh Garden Dalat is a newly launched tourist destination that has quickly become popular among visitors. The garden offers a fairy-tale-like experience with vast flower gardens, dancers amidst the blooms, a windmill adorned with fresh flowers, and charming fairy houses. Visitors can also admire a giant love clock and enjoy the serene atmosphere of a large coffee shop surrounded by flowers. The garden is not very large but is definitely worth exploring for nature and flower enthusiasts.
name: Khu du lịch Fresh Garden Dalat
address: 90B Vạn Thành, Phường 5, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng 670000, Vietnam

detail_description: Suoi Vang Lake, located in Lam Dong Province, Vietnam, is a renowned natural attraction. It is situated in Lac Duong district, just 20 kilometers north of the city of Dalat. The area offers various routes for exploration and adventure. Visitors can take the Pine Tree Road (DT722) to reach the lake and enjoy an excellent asphalt road that extends further north with potential campsites along the way.
name: Suoi Vang Lake
address: Lát, Lạc Dương District, Lam Dong, Vietnam

name: Choy Flower Garden
address: Tà Nung, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

detail_description: Da Lat Pedagogy College, previously known as Lycee Yersin, is a stunning French colonial building in Da Lat. It attracts many young visitors who come to take photos in its front courtyard during weekends. Notable alumni of the college include Norodom Sihanouk, the former King of Cambodia.
name: Da Lat Pedagogy College
address: 29 Yersin, Phường 9, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

detail_description: The statue of the Virgin Mary at Dalat Cathedral is a significant landmark in Vietnam's Central Highlands. The cathedral, constructed in the 1930s with Roman Church architecture, features a towering bell tower and intricate gingerbread-style design. Initially intended for use by French colonial residents and visitors, it was funded through donations collected by Father Nicolas, the local Catholic priest. This iconic site holds historical and religious significance, making it a must-visit destination for travelers exploring the area.
name: The statue of the Virgin Mary at Dalat Cathedral
address: WCPQ+G67, Phường 3, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

detail_description: Dalat Center - New Market is a vibrant and visually appealing market that offers a wide array of produce, meat, flowers, clothes, shoes, souvenirs, fruits, cakes and jams. The daytime market showcases carefully crafted displays with vibrant colors. It's recommended to visit in the evening for a more bustling and fun atmosphere. The market also features listed prices for items such as clothes and shoes to ensure fair pricing for visitors. Additionally, it offers second-hand items at great prices.
name: Dalat Center - New Market
address: Phan Bội Châu, Chợ mới center tần 2, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: Resort set amid pine forests & colorful flower gardens, with restaurants & a 9-hole golf course.
detail_description: Nestled in the picturesque landscapes of Dalat, the Mong Mo Hill Tourist Area is a renowned destination offering a serene retreat amidst pine forests and vibrant flower gardens. This popular spot is celebrated for its dreamy hills adorned with volunteer trees, stone walls, and exotic animals. As a newly-built resort, it boasts an artistic arrangement of villas, lakes, restaurants, and playgrounds. Visitors can also enjoy a 9-hole golf course within this idyllic setting.
name: Mong Mo Hill Tourist Area
address: Số 5 Đường Mai Anh Đào, Phường 8, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng 670000, Vietnam

detail_description: Nestled on the edge of hills in Dalat, Me Linh Coffee Garden offers a unique experience for coffee enthusiasts. The vintage coffee shop allows visitors to savor filter coffee while taking in stunning mountain views and immersing themselves in the local Vietnamese coffee culture. With its open design, patrons can enjoy 360-degree vistas and even explore the small coffee farm nearby.
name: Me Linh Coffee Garden
address: Tổ 20 thôn 4, Tà Nung, Tp. Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng 670000, Vietnam

detail_description: Maze Bar, also known as 100 Rooftop Bar, offers a unique and thrilling experience. Upon arrival, visitors purchase drinks for entry, with cocktails priced at 60,000VND and beers at 40,000VND. The bar's dimly lit ambiance adds to the excitement as guests navigate through narrow passageways and staircases, often losing track of their location within the maze-like structure.
name: Maze Bar
address: 57 Phan Bội Châu, Phường 1, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam

excerpt: Cozy guesthouse with 4 charming suites in a 1935 building, offering an airy restaurant/bar.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Dalat, The Escape Bar & Cafe/Live Music is a cozy and chic spot that offers a vibrant ambiance, tasty cocktails, and excellent live music. Every Saturday night, guests can enjoy an English acoustic music show featuring Tommy from Wasabi Band. The bar is known for its lively atmosphere and is popular among foreigners. With its charming suites in a 1935 building, it's the perfect place to unwind after exploring Dalat's landscapes.
name: The Escape Bar & Cafe/Live Music
address: 2 Đ. Trần Phú, Phường 3, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng 66100, Vietnam

detail_description: Bắc Thang Lên Hỏi Ông Trời, a new virtual destination in Da Lat, offers visitors stunning backgrounds like the Golden Bridge model from Da Nang and the Stairway to Heaven. The place boasts a serene atmosphere and fresh air, making it unnecessary to travel to other famous destinations. With only four landscapes available for visiting, visitors can enjoy drinks and ice cream priced between 30,000-40,000vnd.
name: Bắc Thang Lên Hỏi Ông Trời
address: Tuý Sơn, Xuân Thọ, Đà Lạt, Lâm Đồng, Vietnam
